Bitten by the 90 day exercise window

stories.text:
I'll start: myself and some others have been working on a batteries-included approach for building or augmenting image datasets. Kaggle has an impressive library, but it's a bit spotty when it comes to serving my own hobbies. There have been so many ideas for tools I wanted to build, but never did because I couldn't find a prepped dataset on the Internet and didn't want to bother harvesting it myself.

So, what computer vision projects are y'all working on?

--- If you're working on a project that could benefit from readily available machine-annotated images, you can reach out here: https://gigaimager.com
